<main>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="badge">
      <span class="badge-dot"></span>
      <span id="badge-text">v0.1.0-alpha - based on Folia 26.1.2</span>
    </div>

    <div class="bento">
      <div class="card c3 reveal">
        <span class="section-tag">SilkMC</span>
        <h1>Threaded regions,<br /><span class="accent">fewer immediate plugin failures.</span></h1>
        <p class="hero-sub" style="max-width:none;margin-bottom:1.4rem;">
          SilkMC is a compatibility-focused fork of Folia. The goal is not to fake a single-threaded server again.
          The goal is to keep regional multithreading, make more Paper, Bukkit, and Spigot plugins get further,
          and fail cleanly when a plugin crosses into unsafe behavior.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="btn-primary" id="download-btn" href="https://github.com/tame-gg/SilkMC/releases/latest" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            Get SilkMC
          </a>
          <a class="btn-ghost" href="https://github.com/tame-gg/SilkMC" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            View source
          </a>
        </div>
        <p class="hero-version">
          Use the paperclip jar to run it. Requires Java 25+.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card c3 reveal" style="transition-delay:.04s">
        <span class="section-tag" id="status">Current state</span>
        <div class="card-title">Alpha means alpha</div>
        <p class="card-body">
          There may still be security vulnerabilities, memory leaks, plugin edge cases, and unstable behavior.
          Some plugins will work. Some will partly work. Some will flat-out not work yet.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-metrics" style="margin-top:auto;">
          <div class="hero-metric">
            <span class="metric-val c">Folia</span>
            <span class="metric-label">upstream architecture preserved</span>
          </div>
          <div class="hero-metric">
            <span class="metric-val g">WARN</span>
            <span class="metric-label">default unsupported plugin mode</span>
          </div>
          <div class="hero-metric">
            <span class="metric-val">Paper</span>
            <span class="metric-label">primary compatibility target</span>
          </div>
          <div class="hero-metric">
            <span class="metric-val">Java 25+</span>
            <span class="metric-label">minimum runtime</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card c2 reveal" style="transition-delay:.08s">
        <span class="card-icon">!</span>
        <div class="card-title">What SilkMC does when a plugin goes unsafe</div>
        <p class="card-body">
          Prefer disabling the plugin and logging a direct compatibility warning instead of letting the server hard-crash.
        </p>
        <span class="card-chip">server stability first</span>
      </div>

      <div class="card c2 reveal" style="transition-delay:.12s">
        <span class="card-icon">~</span>
        <div class="card-title">What SilkMC is trying to narrow</div>
        <p class="card-body">
          Scheduler assumptions, lifecycle timing, legacy synchronous expectations, thread ownership mistakes, and async misuse.
        </p>
        <span class="card-chip blue">compatibility work</span>
      </div>

      <div class="card c2 reveal" style="transition-delay:.16s">
        <div class="terminal-card" style="box-shadow:none;background:transparent;border:none;">
          <div class="terminal-bar">
            <div class="terminal-dots"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div>
